'''Matias Fernandez-Pardo''' (born 3 February 2005) is a Belgian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[wide midfielder]] or [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Lille OSC|Lille]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]].

==Early life==
Matias Fernandez-Pardo was born on 3 February 2005 in [[Brussels]], Belgium within a family of Spanish and Italian descent.<ref name="LOSC0824">{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://www.losc.fr/actualites/2024-08-30/le-prometteur-attaquant-belge-matias-fernandez-pardo-est-un-dogue |title=Le prometteur attaquant belge, Matias Fernandez-Pardo est un Dogue |date=30 August 2024 |website=[[Lille OSC|LOSC]] |access-date=30 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240830225926/https://www.losc.fr/actualites/2024-08-30/le-prometteur-attaquant-belge-matias-fernandez-pardo-est-un-dogue |archive-date=30 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He started playing football at [[RSCA Futures|Anderlecht]] and [[K.V. Mechelen|Mechelen]], and then joined French [[Ligue 1]] club [[Lille OSC|Lille]] academy in 2014.<ref name="LOSC0824"/> He stayed in Northern France until 2020 when he chose to come back in Belgium and join [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]] youth system.<ref name="LOSC0824"/>

==Club career==
===Gent===
During the 2022–23 season, he was selected for Jong KAA Gent, the promising team of Gent, where he managed to score two goals in 26 appearances. On 9 March 2023, he made his official debut with Gent's first team: in a Conference League match against [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|Istanbul Başakşehir]] (1–1 draw), coach [[Hein Vanhaezebrouck]] brought him on as a substitute for [[Hugo Cuypers]] in the 85th minute.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/347570|title=Ook AA Gent mag na gelijkspel tegen Basaksehir nog dromen in Conference League: Gift Orban is weer held van de avond &#124; Het Nieuwsblad|work=Het Nieuwsblad }}</ref> On 1 April 2023, he joined the first team in his first league appearance against [[R.F.C. Seraing (1922)|Seraing]] in a match that ended 5–0 for Gent. His first professional goal came in a 5–0 win against [[Royal Charleroi S.C.|Charleroi]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sudinfo.be/id809364/article/2024-03-18/va-jouer-avec-ceux-qui-ont-envie-de-sauver-le-club-le-sporting-de-charleroi-va|title=" On va jouer avec ceux qui ont envie de sauver le club " : le Sporting de Charleroi va jouer sa survie en Pro League lors des Playdowns|date=March 18, 2024|website=sudinfo.be}}</ref>

Fernandez-Pardo signed a contract extension with Gent in June 2023 until mid-2026.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kaagent.be/nl/nieuws/21-06-2023/matias-fernandez-pardo-verlengt-contract|title=Matias Fernandez-Pardo verlengt contract &#124; KAA Gent Website|website=KAA Gent}}</ref> In the 2024 winter transfer window, he was linked with a move to [[US Lecce|Lecce]] or [[Real Valladolid]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.calciolecce.it/2024/01/31/dal-belgio-lecce-interessato-al-18enne-fernandez-pardo/|title=Dal Belgio: Lecce interessato al 18enne Fernández-Pardo|date=January 30, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://onefootball.com/es/noticias/el-valladolid-habria-puesto-el-ojo-en-matias-fernandez-pardo-38967007|title=El Valladolid habría puesto el ojo en Matías Fernández-Pardo|date=August 16, 2024|website=OneFootball}}</ref> After Gent managed to secure a ticket to the [[2024–25 UEFA Conference League|Conference League]], it was reported that [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] was interested in recruiting him.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/duitse-landskampioen-komt-speler-ophalen-bij-kaa-gent-39623474|title='Duitse landskampioen komt speler ophalen bij KAA Gent'|date=June 14, 2024|website=OneFootball}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |language=nl |url=https://www.hln.be/sport-in-de-buurt/fernandez-pardo-de-uitblinker-bij-aa-gent-met-twee-goals-en-een-assist-ik-geniet-vooral-van-mijn-eerste-assist~a3089ea5 |title=Fernandez-Pardo dé uitblinker bij AA Gent met twee goals en een assist: "Ik geniet vooral van mijn eerste assist" |last=De Graeve |first=Sander |date=20 May 2024 |newspaper=[[Het Laatste Nieuws]] |access-date=30 August 2024}}</ref> During the [[2023–24 Belgian Pro League#Europe play-offs|2023–24 Belgian Pro League play-offs]], he played in each of the 10 matches and scored 7 goals, as well as providing two assists.<ref name="LOSC0824"/>

===Lille===
On 30 August 2024, Fernandez-Pardo officially returned to [[Ligue 1]] club [[Lille OSC|Lille]], signing a five-year contract for the club he left as an academy player four years ago.<ref name="LOSC0824"/> According to various columnists and reporters, the financial details of the transfer include an initial and base fee of €10 million and a maximum of €2 million add-ons depending on sporting conditions.<ref>{{cite news |language=nl |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20240830_96876332 |title=Matias Fernandez-Pardo keert terug naar Lille, AA Gent vangt minstens tien miljoen euro: "Droom om Champions League te spelen" |last=Van Damme |first=Michael |date=30 August 2024 |newspaper=[[Het Nieuwsblad]] |access-date=30 August 2024 |archive-date=30 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240830220550/https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20240830_96876332 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://lepetitlillois.com/2024/08/30/mercato-accord-trouve-entre-le-losc-et-le-kaa-gent-pour-matias-fernandez-pardo |title=Mercato : Accord trouvé entre le LOSC et le KAA Gent pour Matias Fernandez-Pardo |last=Marcant |first=Raphaël |date=30 August 2024 |website=Le Petit Lillois |access-date=30 August 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a3280122748528607989-matias-fernandez-pardo-est-proche-du-losc |title=Matias Fernandez-Pardo est proche du LOSC |last1=Aouna |first1=Santi |last2=Denis |first2=Sébastien |date=30 August 2024 |website=Foot Mercato |access-date=30 August 2024}}</ref> On 10 November, he scored his first Ligue 1 goal in a 2–2 draw at [[OGC Nice|Nice]] after a rush on the left wing.<ref>{{cite news |language=fr |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/-je-suis-revenu-car-il-y-a-tout-pour-que-les-jeunes-progressent-ici-fernandez-pardo-un-prometteur-retour-a-lille/1519660 |title=« Je suis revenu car il y a tout pour que les jeunes progressent ici » : Fernandez-Pardo, un prometteur retour à Lille |last=Penot |first=Hervé |date=11 November 2024 |newspaper=[[L'Équipe]] |access-date=1 December 2024}}</ref> On 6 January 2025, Lille revealed that Fernandez-Pardo had suffered a torn ligament in his left ankle in a 1–1 draw against [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] two days prior.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-06 |title=Official {{!}} Lille's Matias Fernandez-Pardo suffers torn ligament - Get French Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2025/official-lilles-matias-fernandez-pardo-suffers-torn-ligament/ |access-date=2025-01-07 |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Belgium, Fernandez-Pardo was eligible to represent Spain, Italy, or Belgium.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voetbalbelgie.be/artikel/kassa-kassa-voor-kaa-gent-fernandez-pardo|title=Kassa, kassa voor KAA Gent: Fernandez-Pardo|website=VoetbalBelgie}}</ref> In November 2023, he was called up by the [[Belgium national under-19 football team|Belgium under-19 team]] for the [[2024 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification|2024 UEFA Euro Under-19 qualifying matches]], and scored the winning brace against [[Albania national under-19 football team|Albania]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kaagent.be/nl/nieuws/20-11-2023/twee-doelpunten-voor-fernandez-pardo|title=Twee doelpunten voor Fernandez-Pardo &#124; KAA Gent Website|website=KAA Gent}}</ref>

On 26 February 2025, Fernandez-Pardo's request to switch allegiance to Spain was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-Change">{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform|accessdate=14 May 2026}}</ref> On 14 March, he was called up by the [[Spain national under-21 football team|Spain national under-21 team]]. In August 2025, he was called up to the [[Spain national under-20 football team|Spain national under-20 team]] for a training in camp in France ahead of the [[2025 FIFA U-20 World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rfef.es/es/noticias/paco-gallardo-cita-24-futbolistas-para-la-concentracion-de-francia-de-septiembre|title= Paco Gallardo cita a 24 futbolistas para la concentración de Francia de septiembre|trans-title=Paco Gallardo names 24 players for September's training camp in France|language=es|publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]]|date=28 August 2025}}</ref> but he withdrew from the squad before the beginning of camp.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rfef.es/es/noticias/matias-fernandez-pardo-baja-en-la-concentracion-de-la-sub-20|title= Matías Fernández-Pardo, baja en la concentración de la sub-20|trans-title=Matías Fernández-Pardo misses U-20 training camp|language=es|publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]]|date=4 September 2025}}</ref> He ultimately never represented Spain at any level.

On 14 May 2026, Fernandez-Pardo's request to switch international allegiance back to Belgium was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-Change"/>

